{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17619302","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17619302"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:30:28+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:30:28+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16549"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16549","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16549"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.23,0.5,0.03,0.17,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9240"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75718"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9240","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9240"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16549"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61236"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"6"},{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"3077"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7124"},{"type":"tags","id":"7125"},{"type":"tags","id":"11340"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21894"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21897"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75718","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75718"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDeep brain stimulation is a neurosurgical treatment for advanced Parkinson\u0027s disease that involves delivering electrical pulses to specific brain regions.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following pairs represents the primary targets for deep brain stimulation in Parkinson\u0027s disease?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["External globus pallidus and subthalamic nucleus","Substantia nigra pars compacta and substantia nigra pars reticulata","Dorsal striatum and external globus pallidus","Internal globus pallidus and subthalamic nucleus","Internal globus pallidus and external globus pallidus"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe primary targets for deep brain stimulation in Parkinson\u0027s disease are the \u003Cstrong\u003Einternal globus pallidus and subthalamic nucleus\u003C/strong\u003E. These structures become hyperactive in Parkinson\u0027s disease due to loss of dopaminergic inhibition, and their stimulation helps restore more normal motor function.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options are incorrect because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExternal globus pallidus and subthalamic nucleus\u003C/strong\u003E - The external globus pallidus is not typically targeted for stimulation\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESubstantia nigra pars compacta and substantia nigra pars reticulata\u003C/strong\u003E - While the substantia nigra is central to Parkinson\u0027s pathophysiology, it is not a usual target for stimulation\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDorsal striatum and external globus pallidus\u003C/strong\u003E - Neither structure is typically targeted for deep brain stimulation\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInternal globus pallidus and external globus pallidus\u003C/strong\u003E - The external globus pallidus is not a usual target for stimulation\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDeep brain stimulation works by disrupting abnormal neural firing patterns in these overactive nuclei, which helps improve motor symptoms of Parkinson\u0027s disease.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Deep brain stimulation for Parkinson\u0027s disease primarily targets the subthalamic nucleus and internal globus pallidus.","Deep brain stimulation works by disrupting abnormal neural signalling patterns in these target areas.","These targets are chosen because they show pathological overactivity in Parkinson\u0027s disease."],"references":["Hariz M, Blomstedt P. Deep brain stimulation for Parkinson\u0027s disease. J Intern Med. 2022 Nov;292(5):764-778. doi: 10.1111/joim.13541. Epub 2022 Jul 13. PMID: 35798568; PMCID: PMC9796446.","Alexander GE. Biology of Parkinson\u0027s disease: pathogenesis and pathophysiology of a multisystem neurodegenerative disorder. Dialogues Clin Neurosci. 2004 Sep;6(3):259-80. doi: 10.31887/DCNS.2004.6.3/galexander. PMID: 22033559; PMCID: PMC3181806","Dickson DW. Parkinson\u0027s disease and parkinsonism: neuropathology. Cold Spring Harb Perspect Med. 2012 Aug 1;2(8):a009258. doi: 10.1101/cshperspect.a009258. PMID: 22908195; PMCID: PMC3405828","Sonne J, Reddy V, Beato MR. Neuroanatomy, Substantia Nigra. 2024 Sep 10. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30725680","Singh, V. (2024). Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61236"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16549"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61236","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61236"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-30T20:22:33+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-30T20:23:32+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9240"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75718"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"6","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/6"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc75","name":"Geriatrics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"